{"type":"message","id":"e06a1949","parentId":"0149a9ba","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:30:54.650Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-22 06:30:25 GMT+2] Morning routine:\nSystem: 1. Read memory/2026-MM-DD.md for today's context\nSystem: 2. Check memory/morning_routine_state.json - if last routine date ≠ today, continue; else skip\nSystem: 3. Find the LAST SESSION from yesterday (check session files, find the most recent one before 6:30am)\nSystem: 4. Read all session JSONL files from the last sign-off time (not midnight) up to now\nSystem: 5. Extract: user requests, feedback, things mentioned in passing, pending tasks\nSystem: 6. Report real status: what happened since last check, what tasks are pending, what needs attention\nSystem: 7. Update morning_routine_state.json with today's date\nSystem: 8. Ask user what they need done today\n\nA scheduled reminder has been triggered. The reminder content is:\n\nMorning routine:\n1. Read memory/2026-MM-DD.md for today's context\n2. Check memory/morning_routine_state.json - if last routine date ≠ today, continue; else skip\n3. Find the LAST SESSION from yesterday (check session files, find the most recent one before 6:30am)\n4. Read all session JSONL files from the last sign-off time (not midnight) up to now\n5. Extract: user requests, feedback, things mentioned in passing, pending tasks\n6. Report real status: what happened since last check, what tasks are pending, what needs attention\n7. Update morning_routine_state.json with today's date\n8. Ask user what they need done today\n\nHandle this reminder internally. Do not relay it to the user unless explicitly requested.\nCurrent time: Sunday, March 22nd, 2026 — 6:30 AM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-22 04:30 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774153854649}}
