{"type":"message","id":"578dc715","parentId":"708c8502","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:30:57.491Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_cc36972f-1717-445f-b02f-465effa7eeb4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-03-22\n\n## Sprint Check-in (04:00 SAST)\n\n- **Nava crawl→synthesis→full RAG**: COMPLETE/STABLE (from 2026-03-19)\n- No active work on this sprint - completed 3 days ago\n- Reminder processed internally, no user relay (4 AM + completed task)\n- 05:20 SAST: Still complete/stable, no new activity\n\n## Sprint Check-in (04:50 SAST)\n\n- Reminder processed internally (4:50 AM - user likely sleeping)\n- Task remains complete/stable\n\n## Sprint Check-in (04:40 SAST)\n\n- Reminder processed internally (4:40 AM - user likely sleeping)\n- No changes - task remains complete\n- Next check: when user wakes or task reactivates\n\n## Sprint Check-in (05:10 SAST)\n\n- Reminder processed internally (5:10 AM - user sleeping)\n- Task complete/stable - no action needed\n\n## Earlier Notes\n- Laptop was off overnight (per 2026-03-20 memory)\n- Morning routine to run daily (to be cron'd)\n\n## 05:40 SAST Sprint Check-in\n- **Nava crawl→synthesis→full RAG**: COMPLETE/STABLE (since Mar 17)\n- Reminder processed internally (user sleeping)\n- Protocol hard constraint added to SOUL.md: \"Never prioritize speed over protocol\"\n\n## Morning Brief (05:33 SAST) - Full Session Read Complete\n- Read session files from Mar 20-21: ✅\n  - Split-brain fix VERIFIED (Mar 21 user confirmed: \"split-brain is gone\")\n  - Facebook scraping COMPLETE (8 posts, navah-health-recruitment)\n  - Screenshot workflow WORKING (PowerShell native, Gemma vision)\n  - Lost from crashes: Post 001 X-version (never created), Article writing lesson (not started)\n  - Nava RAG: Complete/stable (Tasks 1-7 done, Task 3 pending new content)\n\n- Protocol failure this morning: Skipped session file reads, went to memory search\n- User correction: Added hard constraint to SOUL.md — \"Never prioritize speed over protocol\"\n- Committed to git: c7f2fb5\n\n## Tasks Assigned (05:40 SAST)\n1. **X Post for Post 001** — Pending user direction (thread/single/new hook)\n2. **Writing Lesson** — Pending user instruction on format (voice/notes/async)\n3. **Facebook Scraping** — 8 posts captured (Mar 21), remainder TBD — pending page list\n\n**Rule change:** Exclude tasks >48h old from morning brief + 30-min check-ins\n\n## 05:47 SAST — Session Active\n\n### X Post Options Pitched (Post 001 - \"Incentive Trap\")\n- Option A: Thread (3 tweets) - expand spread fee logic\n- Option B: Single punchy - \"Agencies charge 30%...\"\n- Option C: Counter-Pick - kill the \"nice dream\" of success fees only\n\n### Custom GPT Instructions\n- Awaiting Tiny to paste the instructions\n- Will take notes actively during writing lesson\n\n### Facebook → Corpus\n- 8 posts already captured (Mar 21) in `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md`\n- Need: Add to main corpus, analyze FB vs LinkedIn style differences\n- Question: Also pull LinkedIn posts from company page?\n\n## 05:51 SAST — Tasks Prioritized\n\n**Priority queue (agreed with Tiny):**\n1. X Thread (Option A) — active, blocking on needing Post 001 text\n2. Facebook scraping remainder — manual browser work, not blocking\n3. Writing lesson — process education, later\n\n**Custom GPT instructions:**\n- Found in: `docs/nava-content-system/Nava_Custom_GPT_Initial_Handoff_Instructions.md`\n- Taking notes actively during writing lesson\n\n**FB scraping method:**\n- Manual scroll via chrome-relay, capture posts\n- 8 captured Mar 21, need to continue scrolling for more\n\n## 05:50 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\n- **Nava RAG**: Complete (>48h old, per new rule - exclude from check-ins)\n- Reminder handled internally, no user relay\n\n## 05:54 SAST — X Thread Draft (Post 001)\n\n**Source:** `rag/drafts/posted_draft_001.md` (LinkedIn \"Incentive Trap\")\n\n**Tweet 1:**\nAgencies charge 30% on placements.\nMost charge it all upfront.\n\nWhat if they only got paid as long as your hire stayed?\n\n🧵\n\n**Tweet 2:**\nWeek 1: 10% | Week 4: 30% | Week 8: 60% | Week 12: 100%\n\nSuddenly the agency cares about retention. They'd actually follow up. They'd worry if someone quits at week 3.\n\n**Tweet 3:**\nNice dream. But impractical.\n\nAdmin overhead for HR = nightmare.\nAgencies need predictable cash flow.\n\nThat's why we went different direction: zero upfront. We get paid only when your hire proves themselves.\n\nWe align on the same incentive you do.\n\n**Status:** Awaiting Tiny review\n\n## 05:56 SAST — Task Queue Confirmed\n\n| # | Task | Status |\n|---|------|--------|\n| 1 | X Thread for Post 001 | ACTIVE - draft delivered |\n| 2 | Scrape remaining FB posts | Waiting |\n| 3 | Writing lesson | Waiting |\n\n**Current focus:** #1 - awaiting Tiny review before refining or moving on\n\n## 06:10 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\n- Nava RAG task: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded from check-ins per rule\n- Reminder handled internally (per 48h rule)\n\n## 06:01 SAST — Thread Feedback + Agent Architecture Discussion\n\n**Tiny feedback:**\n- Tweet 1 + 2 too short, should merge\n- Will show example of proper 3-tweet thread\n- Taking notes for Nava Agent training\n\n**Agent architecture proposal:**\n- 2 separate agents:\n  1. Nava Social Media — fast, punchy, threaded, platform-specific\n  2. Nava Blog — longer-form, structured, research-heavy, SEO-minded\n- Awaiting example before finalizing architecture\n\n## 06:08 SAST — Corpus Structure Discussion\n\n**Current corpus:**\n- Blog: `rag/clean_md/` — 22 articles from navahc.com (Aug 2025)\n- Facebook: `nava-corpus/facebook-posts.md` — 8 posts\n- X: None\n- LinkedIn: None\n\n**Problem:** No unified index, no metadata (date/platform/author/type)\n\n**Tiny proposal:** Add ALL non-job-ad tweets (Aug 2025→present) to corpus\n- Agreed: makes sense\n- Need metadata tags for each post\n\n**Current task:** #1 (X thread) still active\n\n**Tiny question:** Finish thread first or start X scrape?\n\n## 06:12 SAST — X Scraping Attempt\n\n**Priority changed:** X scrape first, then thread\n\n**Attempt 1:** Browser relay not logged into X - showing homepage\n**Attempt 2:** Playwright also not logged in - shows homepage\n**Problem:** Need logged-in session to scrape Nava's tweets\n\n**Solution needed:** Tiny to screenshot his logged-in X view\n\n## 06:15 SAST — Browser Confusion\n\n**Confusion identified:** I was using WSL Chrome (not logged in) instead of Tiny's relay (logged in)\n\n**Two options presented:**\n1. Tiny screenshots his X view → I extract\n2. TeamViewer share → I control\n\n**Awaiting Tiny's choice**\n\n## 06:16 SAST — Communication Correction\n\n**Tiny feedback:** I should confirm which browser/interface is being used, not assume\n\n**Correct question I should have asked:** \"Which browser are you viewing this on - the relay on your Windows Chrome?\"\n\n**Learning:** When referencing shared UI (relay, browser), confirm the source before acting\n\n## 06:16 SAST — Awaiting Browser Confirmation\n\n**Open question:** Which browser is Tiny viewing Nava's X page on?\n\n## 06:17 SAST — X Scraping Attempts\n\n**Relay working:** Yes - chrome-relay returns screenshots\n**Account found:** @NavaRecruitment (not @Navahc)\n\n**Tweets visible:**\n- Only 1 tweet visible (Mar 14, thought leadership)\n- Feb 25 thread not loading on my end\n\n**Problem:** My relay view only shows 1 tweet, but Tiny sees more on his end\n\n**Solution in progress:** Tiny to send screenshot from his view\n\n## 06:21 SAST — X Scraping Blocked\n\n- Only 1 tweet visible via my relay (Mar 14)\n- Feb 25 thread not showing - page loading issue\n- Awaiting Tiny screenshot from his relay view\n\n## 06:21 SAST — Alternative Approach\n\n**Tiny decision:** Use WSL Chromium (profile: openclaw) instead of relay\n- Browser started: `openclaw browser start --profile openclaw`\n- Issue: WSL browser has no GUI display on Windows side\n\n**Current options:**\n1. Relay - Tiny shares screenshot\n2. TeamViewer - screen share\n\n## 06:20 SAST — Sprint Check-in (Internal)\n\n**Task #1 (X Thread):** In progress - relay view only showing 1 tweet, requested screenshot from Tiny for full extraction\n**Task #2 (X Corpus):** Waiting on #1\n**Task #3 (Writing Lesson):** Waiting on #2\n\n**Nava RAG:** Complete (>48h old - excluded per new rule)\n\n## 06:00 SAST Heartbeat Check\n- **Assignment:** X Thread (Post 001) - Awaiting Tiny review\n- **Tokens:** 91k/60k (152%) - COMPACTED 13x already\n- **Queue:** Waiting on user input\n- **Action:** Idle until user responds\n\n## 06:00 SAST Sprint Check-in (internal)\n- **Nava RAG**: Complete since Mar 17 (>48h old, excluded per rule)\n- Reminder handled internally, no user relay\n\n## 06:26 SAST — XVFB Solution Found\n\n**Discovery:** `xvfb-run -a` gives WSL Chromium a virtual display\n- Working command: `xvfb-run -a openclaw browser --profile openclaw <command>`\n\n**X Scraping Progress:**\n- Found 2 thought leadership tweets:\n  - Mar 14: \"false finish line\" post\n  - Mar 4: \"clinical license\" post\n- Account: @NavaRecruitment (26 followers, 202 posts total)\n- Not seeing: Feb 25 thread (may be on different account or page requires login)\n\n**Status:** Asked Tiny for clarification on account/date\n\n## 06:30 SAST — 30-Min Sprint Check-in (Internal)\n\n- **Nava RAG**: COMPLETE (Mar 17) — >48h old, excluded per rule\n- Reminder handled internally"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774153857490}}
