{"type":"message","id":"c8538167","parentId":"e1d69376","timestamp":"2026-03-22T04:31:21.473Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"ollama_call_14b4ee52-3a6b-4279-8555-df5c90d83a6b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f9c1e896\",\"parentId\":\"85eda69f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:33.905Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Pre-compaction memory flush. Store durable memories only in memory/2026-03-21.md (create memory/ if needed). Treat workspace bootstrap/reference files such as MEMORY.md, SOUL.md, TOOLS.md, and AGENTS.md as read-only during this flush; never overwrite, replace, or edit them. If memory/2026-03-21.md already exists, APPEND new content only and do not overwrite existing entries. Do NOT create timestamped variant files (e.g., 2026-03-21-HHMM.md); always use the canonical 2026-03-21.md filename. If nothing to store, reply with NO_REPLY.\\nCurrent time: Saturday, March 21st, 2026 — 12:07 PM (Africa/Johannesburg) / 2026-03-21 10:07 UTC\"}],\"timestamp\":1774087653902}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"c6f7b414\",\"parentId\":\"f9c1e896\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:37.674Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"ollama_call_85f60721-2fd7-462c-9be2-dc8aa4b9c1c1\",\"name\":\"read\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"memory/2026-03-21.md\"}}],\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.5:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":21459,\"output\":163,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":21622,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1774087657673}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"15ffe0a2\",\"parentId\":\"c6f7b414\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:37.713Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_85f60721-2fd7-462c-9be2-dc8aa4b9c1c1\",\"toolName\":\"read\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"# 2026-03-21\\n\\n## Morning Brief Delivered (2026-03-21 11:26 SAST)\\n\\n- Provided morning brief covering Arsenal (wrong info - user corrected me), F1 (no race this weekend), project status\\n- **Correction needed**: Arsenal fixture info was incorrect; user flagged it\\n- User asked: \\\"Did you read all the sessions from yesterday?\\\" — No, I hadn't\\n- User also asked how I check Arsenal fixtures (via web search) — methodology exposed the gap\\n\\n## Session Review Needed\\n\\n- Multiple sessions from March 20 exist in `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/`\\n- Last session before today was ~10:00 UTC on March 20\\n- Key session noted: `371c2e0a-e697-4a30-983e-55e5ff7d4f94` (most recent from today)\\n- From sessions_list output, saw context crashes on March 19-20 due to token limits\\n- Split-brain fix was applied (global scope in config) but verification needed\\n\\n## Actions Pending\\n\\n1. Read full transcript from March 20 sessions to catch up properly\\n2. Verify Arsenal fixture with correct source\\n3. Confirm split-brain fix is working in current session\\n\\n## Sprint Status (from 2026-03-17.md)\\n\\n- Core RAG: Complete\\n- Task 3 (ingestion): Pending new Nava content\\n- Voice note: Still pending transcription\\n\\n## Morning Brief Correction (2026-03-21 11:33 SAST)\\n\\n- **Initial brief had wrong Arsenal fixture** — claimed today vs Wolves, actually:\\n  - **No match today** (March 21)\\n  - **Next: Sun March 22** — Arsenal vs Manchester City (Carabao Cup Final), 6:30 PM SAST\\n- Root cause: Used stale search results, didn't verify with live fixture list\\n- User called it out correctly\\n\\n## Key Learning: Session Reading Protocol (2026-03-21 11:38 SAST)\\n\\n- **User expectation**: Read actual transcript files from `~/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/` using `read` tool\\n- **Failure**: Used memory_search instead of reading session files directly\\n- **Result**: Got incomplete/out-of-date context, made errors in morning brief\\n- **Rule for future**: When asked \\\"did you read sessions from X day\\\", fetch the actual JSONL files, not just search memory\\n\\n## Session File Reading Confirmed (2026-03-21 11:40 SAST)\\n\\n- Read session file `36da5e41-d038-4c2e-87ad-3477fd17181d.jsonl` (March 20)\\n- Confirmed split-brain fix VERIFIED: WebUI showed full context from TUI session\\n- User comment: \\\"No, I am convinced the split-brain is gone!\\\"\\n- LinkedIn activity review: Yosef's oldest post ~May 2025\\n\\n## Corrected Arsenal Fixture (2026-03-21)\\n\\n- **No match** on March 21\\n- **Next: Sun March 22** vs Manchester City (Carabao Cup Final), 6:30 PM SAST\\n- Verified via live session data, not stale search\\n\\n## Lost Session Data Issue (2026-03-21 11:48 SAST)\\n\\n- User asked about NurseSphere/article writing lesson discussion from March 20\\n- **NOT FOUND** in session files despite multiple search approaches\\n- Root cause: Multiple context crashes on March 19-20 due to token limits\\n- **X version of post 001** was never created (noted at 11:50 SAST March 20 before crash)\\n- User frustrated: \\\"we were about to start something yesterday and there is also at least 1 task I did not complete\\\"\\n- Lesson: Session file extraction works but content may be lost or stored in non-text formats during crashes\\n\\n## 30-Minute Sprint Check-in (2026-03-21 11:52 SAST)\\n\\n- Reminder received and handled internally\\n- Current focus: Resolving lost session data / finding NurseSphere discussion\\n- RAG status unchanged from prior: Core RAG complete, Task 3 pending new content\\n- No new Nava articles detected for ingestion\\n\\n## Confirmed Incomplete Tasks (2026-03-21 12:00 SAST)\\n\\nUser confirmed two pending tasks that didn't get done due to context crashes:\\n1. **X version of post 001** — LinkedIn post 001 was ready, X derivative was never created\\n2. **Article writing lesson** — User was about to teach how they write articles, session crashed before it started\\n\\nThese are now officially recorded as pending work.\"}],\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774087657708}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"a2723451\",\"parentId\":\"15ffe0a2\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:41.191Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"ollama_call_20d6bca3-334c-434c-a1be-94d39dbbbd1f\",\"name\":\"edit\",\"arguments\":{\"path\":\"memory/2026-03-21.md\",\"oldText\":\"These are now officially recorded as pending work.\",\"newText\":\"These are now officially recorded as pending work.\\n\\n## Split Brain Root Cause Identified (2026-03-21 12:05 SAST)\\n\\nFound in TinyBackUp/20260320 config:\\n```json\\n\\\"session\\\": {\\n  \\\"scope\\\": \\\"global\\\",\\n  \\\"dmScope\\\": \\\"main\\\"\\n}\\n```\\nThis configuration caused WhatsApp to have its own session scope while TUI used \\\"main\\\" — they never synced context. The fix was setting \\\"scope\\\": \\\"global\\\" in config.\"}}],\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.5:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":22491,\"output\":206,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":22697,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1774087661191}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"a22e0ac8\",\"parentId\":\"a2723451\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:41.220Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"ollama_call_20d6bca3-334c-434c-a1be-94d39dbbbd1f\",\"toolName\":\"edit\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Successfully replaced text in memory/2026-03-21.md.\"}],\"details\":{\"diff\":\"    ...\\n 76 User confirmed two pending tasks that didn't get done due to context crashes:\\n 77 1. **X version of post 001** — LinkedIn post 001 was ready, X derivative was never created\\n 78 2. **Article writing lesson** — User was about to teach how they write articles, session crashed before it started\\n 79 \\n-80 These are now officially recorded as pending work.\\n+80 These are now officially recorded as pending work.\\n+81 \\n+82 ## Split Brain Root Cause Identified (2026-03-21 12:05 SAST)\\n+83 \\n+84 Found in TinyBackUp/20260320 config:\\n+85 ```json\\n+86 \\\"session\\\": {\\n+87   \\\"scope\\\": \\\"global\\\",\\n+88   \\\"dmScope\\\": \\\"main\\\"\\n+89 }\\n+90 ```\\n+91 This configuration caused WhatsApp to have its own session scope while TUI used \\\"main\\\" — they never synced context. The fix was setting \\\"scope\\\": \\\"global\\\" in config.\",\"firstChangedLine\":80},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1774087661215}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"fae09a50\",\"parentId\":\"a22e0ac8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:42.461Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"NO_REPLY\"}],\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"api\":\"ollama\",\"provider\":\"ollama\",\"model\":\"minimax-m2.5:cloud\",\"usage\":{\"input\":22679,\"output\":41,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":22720,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"timestamp\":1774087662459}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f08ffb8f\",\"parentId\":\"fae09a50\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:44.748Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"gateway-client\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"openclaw-tui\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n[Sat 2026-03-21 12:07 GMT+2] Read all of the sessions created betwen 17 March and today. It may be that the discussion I mean is in a session that I used yesterday but was actually created the day before. I need you to know what NurseSphere is before we continue. We discussed post 002! This discussion is important and should've been in your memories!\"}],\"timestamp\":1774087664745}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"f58598f1\",\"parentId\":\"f08ffb8f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-21T10:07:47.261Z\",\"message\":{\